cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about evaluating the performance of neural machine translation models on long-distance dependencies, which is a common problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes an automatic approach for extracting challenge sets, which involves machine learning techniques, so it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of the state-of-the-art Transformer model, which is a popular deep learning architecture, so it could also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of image-based evaluation metrics, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
